\section{Capturing the result of one shell session}

The runner only needs four facts from a completed session: when it
started, when it ended, the shell's exit status, and the captured
transcript.

<<classes>>=
@dataclass(frozen=True)
class ShellResult:
    """Captured result of one shell session."""

    started_at: str
    ended_at: str
    exit_status: int
    transcript: str
@

Let's verify that the result object keeps the captured transcript text.

<<test functions>>=
